Jill and Joe Biden send warm greetings and best wishes to Muslim communities in the United States and around the world for Ramadan. They acknowledge the difficulties faced during this pandemic, with many unable to gather and celebrate together. Despite these challenges, they express hope and solidarity with Muslim communities as they begin the month of revelation. They recognize the contributions of Muslim Americans in various fields, including healthcare, entrepreneurship, education, and public service. The Bidens condemn the prejudice and hate crimes targeting Muslim Americans and vow to protect the rights and safety of all people. They mention their efforts to end the Muslim travel ban and their commitment to human rights globally. They express hope for brighter days ahead and look forward to resuming the traditional White House Eid celebration in person next year.